## Enumerations

### enum  {#ab9298a0662bef8856087aae491e84790}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype="enum llvm::MemDepResult::DepType ">

<EnumerationList title="Enumeration values">

<Link id="ab9298a0662bef8856087aae491e84790a7cb2cbf4079b61ed98784f9fe153c9aa" />
<EnumerationListItem name="Invalid">
Clients of MemDep never see this (= 0)
</EnumerationListItem>

<Link id="ab9298a0662bef8856087aae491e84790a22789038753868da92742bca54389f13" />
<EnumerationListItem name="Clobber">
This is a dependence on the specified instruction which clobbers the desired value
</EnumerationListItem>

<Link id="ab9298a0662bef8856087aae491e84790a1761e14f49db6d6f5c342ad4d0117b37" />
<EnumerationListItem name="Def">
This is a dependence on the specified instruction which defines or produces the desired memory location
</EnumerationListItem>

<Link id="ab9298a0662bef8856087aae491e84790aaa9b5488803947feba51dd5f638d9727" />
<EnumerationListItem name="Other">
This marker indicates that the query has no known dependency in the specified block
</EnumerationListItem>

</EnumerationList>

Definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/analysis/memorydependenceanalysis-h/#l00037">37</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/analysis/memorydependenceanalysis-h">MemoryDependenceAnalysis.h</a>.

<MemberDefinition
  prototype="enum llvm::MemDepResult::OtherType ">
If DepType is &quot;Other&quot;, the upper part of the sum type is an encoding of the following more detailed type information.

<EnumerationListItem name="NonLocal">

</EnumerationListItem>
